Health workers union Hospersa has slammed the Free State Health Department for terminating contracts of close to a hundred community workers. BLOEMFONTEIN - Health workers union Hospersa has slammed the Free State Health Department for terminating contracts of close to 100 community workers. The provincial health department says the decision is because the workers have criminal records, but the union says the records are for minor offences related to community unrest and protests. COVID-19 in SA: Alcohol's impact on the public health system Hospersa's Kevin Halama said the union believes the decision taken by the provincial government is unlawful and unfair. Halama also said the Department was aware of the minor offences on the records of the contract employees. Watch the full interview with Hospersa's Kevin Halama in the video above.  - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.